<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Your OTP account is waiting on you</title>
</head>
<body style="margin:0;padding:0;background:#f5f5f7;font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;color:#1a1a1a;line-height:1.6;">
  <div style="max-width:560px;margin:0 auto;padding:40px 24px;">

    <div style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:32px;">
      <div style="display:inline-block;padding:6px 12px;background:#0f766e;color:white;border-radius:6px;font-size:14px;font-weight:600;">OTP</div>
    </div>

    <h1 style="font-size:22px;font-weight:700;margin:0 0 20px 0;line-height:1.3;">Your OTP account is waiting on you.</h1>

    <p style="margin:0 0 16px 0;font-size:16px;">Hi <%= firstName %>,</p>

    <p style="margin:0 0 16px 0;font-size:16px;">You created an account at orgtp.com about <%= staleDays %> days ago and the next move is still unmade. The next move is publishing your first OOS file. That is the one document where your org's coordination patterns live so agents can read them.</p>

    <p style="margin:0 0 16px 0;font-size:16px;"><strong>If your team has any AI agents in production, you already have an unwritten OOS.</strong> The hard part is just naming it. Three sections is enough to start:</p>

    <ol style="margin:0 0 24px 0;padding-left:22px;font-size:16px;">
      <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">Who the agents are.</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">Who decides when they conflict.</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">The rules nobody wants relearned.</li>
    </ol>

    <p style="margin:0 0 24px 0;font-size:16px;">Three places to pick up where you left off:</p>

    <ul style="margin:0 0 24px 0;padding-left:22px;font-size:16px;">
      <li style="margin-bottom:8px;"><a href="https://orgtp.com/dashboard" style="color:#0f766e;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;">Open your dashboard</a> -- the workspace flow guides you through</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom:8px;"><a href="https://orgtp.com/dashboard/oos-operating-plan" style="color:#0f766e;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;">Start the OOS Operating Plan</a> -- 8 sections, structured fields, recommends owners</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom:8px;"><a href="https://orgtp.com/browse" style="color:#0f766e;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;">See what others published</a> -- a way to start from the answer instead of the blank page</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="margin:0 0 16px 0;font-size:16px;">If something specific is blocking you, hit reply and tell me. I read every one.</p>

    <p style="margin:0 0 32px 0;font-size:16px;">-- David Steel, founder</p>

    <hr style="border:none;border-top:1px solid #e5e5e5;margin:32px 0;">

    <p style="font-size:13px;color:#777;margin:0 0 8px 0;">
      You are receiving this because you signed up at orgtp.com.
    </p>
    <p style="font-size:13px;color:#777;margin:0;">
      <a href="<%- locals.unsubUrl || ('https://orgtp.com/api/v1/newsletter/unsubscribe/' + encodeURIComponent(email)) %>" style="color:#777;">Unsubscribe</a>
    </p>

  </div>
</body>
</html>
